Например, suppose you have a function that accepts a `number` and returns a `string`, and you want to ensure that the returned value will always be a string. In this case, you can use the `any` type to restrict the possible types of the returned value:
```typescript
function foo(num: number): string {
  return String(num);
}
```
In this example, the `num` parameter can have any type, but the returned value will always be a `string`, so the `any` type is used to restrict the possible types of the returned value.

